commit.message:
Set up match prefix mirroring for current tab

Forgot to actually set up the match prefix to mirror the target when the user
adds a hotkey for the current tab (#59). Luckily I had already factored this
out into a nice little function we can just call. Sweet!

Remove unnecessary chrome.tabs.query calls

The one in createNewTab is definitely doing nothing; the tabs parameter of the
callback isn't used. I'm 95% sure changing from the chrome.tabs.query to using
the current tab from tab history will not change the behavior in
closeCurrentTab, but we'll find out soon enough if there are edge cases where
it does.

Add "hotkey for current tab" button (closes #59)

Adds a button right next to "Add hotkey" in options that adds a hotkey
prefilled with the current tab's URL.

Enable the content script in iframes (fixes #25).

Simple 2-line manifest change, though it's not a complete solution (see #61).

Make CSS KT-specific to not collide with websites

There are at least a few websites I noticed problems on, one of which was
articles (not the main page) on androidauthority.com. This is a quick fix, a
bit ugly to add #keeptabs_overlay before everything. We should move to Sass or
Less at some point anyway, and then our CSS will be cleaner.

Update overlay z-index to ridiculously high value

Just discovered that the search UI gets covered up by YouTube's search bar and
menu sidebar (menu is only on the homepage), which have a z-index of
1,999,999,999. The overlay's z-index has thus been increased to 2 billion. Let
the war begin.

Fix update hotkeys on options save

Fixes a bug preventing hotkeys from being reloaded correctly in the background
script upon options save. The bug was introduced in f03b5e when
HOLD_KEY_DEFAULT was changed to HOLD_KEY_EMPTY without checking that all its
uses were also changed over.

closes #5 Real-time invalid hotkey input handling

Cleaned up code.

Hotkey input validation bug fixes

Real-time invalid hotkey input handling.

Fix minor options css bug

When you had no hotkey entries, the header row of the table was smushed
together because of the negative margin on the checkbox column headers. I just
applied the CSS for the width of the actual data rows to the headers as well.

Remove Foundation CSS file

Forgot to do this earlier. We no longer use Foundation at all -- yay!

Detect OS and set default hold key (closes #43)

I moved the manual hold key selection into an advanced section (closes #49) of
options.

Mark unsaved when hold key choice is changed

This was working a few commits back, but I deleted the line that added the
listener to all INPUTTABLE elements, thinking it was unnecessary because such
listeners are already added to each row as they're added. I forgot we still
need to add the listener to the hold key choice <select> element.
Add restore button for deleted hotkeys in options

Implement new hold key system (closes #15)

Also closes #1 and officially removes Escape and Context menu key as hold key
choices. This implements Roger's proposed solution from the discussion on issue
15, as well as some fixes to prevent blocking native shortcuts and reduce
sticking as much as possible with the new system.
Remove dead code

Fix close button for popup and chrome://extensions

We have to use two different methods for them, and that required detecting when
we're in the popup, but it works.
Activate hold key normally on tab search cancel

Make overlay CSS more consistent

A few small changes in response to observed examples of individual sites' CSS
overriding and making inconsistent the styling of the overlay.

Implement over-screen tab search UI (closes #27)

Also closes #16. This commit also changes the popup action from tab search to
options page (which closes #19). I performed rather crude surgery to glue the
hotkeys.js and tab_search.js (and corresponding CSS) together; I'll need to
clean this up a lot when I refactor to use modules (#51).

Add unsaved options warning on close (part of #26)

Unfortunately, there's no way to give the warning when the user closes the
window in general, but we can at least do it when they use our "Close" button.
The button also displays when there are unsaved changes with different text. I
want to get the save and close buttons to float and always stay on screen, but
I can't get position: fixed to work within the extension options page. Since
we're going to be moving the options to the popup anyway (#19), I'll try it
then.

Remove code for legacy options

All current users must have checked out the previous commit and resaved their
options with it before checking out this commit, or their options won't load.

Change options structure (requires resave options)

All current users must checkout this commit, open their options, and resave
them before checking out the next commit. The next commit removes the code for
handling the legacy version of options.

This commit moves the unintuitive "deduplicate" to its inverse, "Always open
new tab"; it also adds a new option, "Use target as match prefix", which does
what it says.

Remove Foundation and background img from options

The start of cleaning up the options page UI (#20).
Remove unused Foundation stuff

Finish styling of hold key indicator (closes #48)

Tried to keep the CSS relatively minimal, and only tested on a few sites. Very
likely we'll have to add more normalizing CSS to keep the indicator looking
exactly the same across sites in the future, but that can be done as
discrepancies are discovered.
Remove extraneous debugging console.log

Display automatic URL changes on save in options

Display automatic URL adjustments to Target and Match Prefix fields immediately
upon save, rather than silently showing up the next time the user opens
options. Part of UI cleanup, issue #20.
Clarify the meaning of "*://" in options help text

Add automatic URL cleanup for options

- Automatically prepend "http://" when the scheme is not specified in a Target
- Automatically append "/" to bare domains; remove the validation requiring the
  user to do this
- (Continue to) automatically prepend "*://" when the scheme is not specified
  in a match prefix

Add hotkey characters display (part of #48)

Just simple white text within the dark overlay box for now. Again, still need
polishing before this feature can be considered done.
